post_text:
Minnesota Department of Education released guidance to Food Service sponsors on September 4th, 2020, allowing them to run a Summer Food Service Program (SFSP) through December 31st, 2020 or until funds are exhausted. This program offers free Breakfast & Lunch to all kids.

Sleepy Eye Public Schools has set up a daily pick up site at the Elementary front doors from 9-10am for students not attending on site. It is very helpful to know ahead of time if you will be partaking in the meals. Sign up is not required, but appreciated, and can be sent via email to taher@sleepyeye.mntm.org.

It is important to note that Free & Reduced applications still need to be completed and turned into the district office. This is very important so please turn in as soon as possible.

Please let me know if you have any questions!

Abby Grove Taher Food Service Director taher@sleepyeye.mntm.org 507-822-1777

Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals. The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit.

Learn more at: www.mn.p-ebt.org

post_text:
Update 4/23/2020: Governor Waltz today at his 2:00PM press conference announced that all public schools in Minnesota remain closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year and continue with their distance learning plan. Sleepy Eye Public School will continue to deliver instruction the same manner as we have done the past three weeks. Our last distance learning day will be on Friday, May 15, 2020. We will also continue our Tier 1 and Tier 2 essential employee daycare services and our daily food delivery and on-site pick up until the end of the school year. We have been also instructed not have distance learning on Friday, May 1st and 4th instead use these days for planning purposes. I emailed Commissioner Ricker and asked for permission to continue delivering instruction since our last school day of May 15 is fast approaching and I prefer not losing any additional instructional days. I will let you know what the Commissioner’s response as soon as I hear back from her.

Stay Safe Everyone!

John Cselovszki

Will be streamed live on the Districts
Facebook page

Wednesday, April 8, 2020
5:30 pm

Due to the current federal and state emergency declarations and guidance about limiting person-to-person contact due to the COVID-19 (coronavirus) pandemic, by action of the school board of Sleepy Eye Public School, all future meetings of the Sleepy Eye Board of Education will be conducted in accordance with Minnesota Statutes 13D.021—Meetings by Telephone or Other Electronic Means—until further notice. One or more board members may participate by telephone or other electronic means. In accordance with Minnesota Statutes 13D.021, members of the public are not permitted to attend this meeting due to the current health pandemic. Persons may monitor this meeting from a remote location as it will be streamed on the school district Facebook page.

Sheila Wurtzberger, Clerk ISD #84
March 7, 2020

Dear Parents,

We received two school related directives from Governor Waltz.

First, he placed a Shelter in Home directive for the State of Minnesota from Friday March 27th through Friday April 10th.

Second, the Governor directed school districts to start executing our distance learning plan from Monday March 30 through Thursday April 30th. Teachers will need to be in the building on Friday May 1st and May 4th to start the transitioning process back to school. At this time his plan is to have students return on May 5th.

Stay Safe!!

Mr. Cselovszki

Minnesota State High School League Update:

Effectively Immediately Friday, March 13, 2020 10:45 a.m.
The Minnesota State High School League is immediately cancelling the Girls Basketball State Tournament.

Additionally, all Boys Section and State Basketball Tournaments have been cancelled.

Section Speech Tournament events for the week of March 15-21 have been postponed indefinitely.

Additional details and information on other upcoming events including Spring Activities will be shared later today.

Please see https://legacy.mshsl.org/mshsl/ for more information.

post_text:
Grandparents Day Sign Up
We are gearing up for Grandparents Day 2020, and are excited to present a new format for this year. We are inviting all grandparents to join us for breakfast, a tour of the school, and viewing of your student's school year portfolio. Grandparents and students will have the opportunity to sit down and enjoy a meal in the cafeteria. Your grandchild will then give you a tour of the school highlighting some of their favorite activities during the school day. Sorry-our space is limited, so parents and siblings cannot attend this event. Please help us in our planning by filling out the following information if your child will have grandparents attending. RSVP no later than Friday, April 3, 2020.

Event date: April 8th starting at 9:30 and ending at 11:30.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScxlH-UwcFO-VvnVcazpEhrEfZ7kIIxdLzmpcT3mMAiRWKlNA/viewform

post_text:
Coronavirus related information:
Sleepy Eye Public School takes the potential Coronavirus epidemic very seriously. We are in daily contact with the Department of Health and the Centers for Disease Control (CDC) as well as the Minnesota Department of Education (MDE). We are taking precautionary measures like reviewing the importance of hand-washing with our elementary students. Mr. Domeier and his custodial staff are working to ensure the common areas and classrooms are sprayed down daily to help from any germs spreading. We ask our families to review basic hand-washing, coughing into the inside elbow, and other techniques to minimize the risk of transmitting any kind of virus. We also ask that families do their best to keep their children home when they are sick, for the duration of the illness. As conditions continue to develop, we will take the guidance of the Department of Health and the CDC and MDE, and will keep you informed to the best of our ability.

Sincerely,
John Cselovszki
Superintendent of School
